      "message": "When handling a forward SYN associated with the current active SFDP session (i.e. SYN re-transmission during 3-way handshake), I am fine with a session re-use.\n\nHowever, if a SFDP session is in TIME_WAIT state and we receive a forward SYN associated with a newer session, then re-using the same SFDP session slot would not be correct. Re-using the slot would mean re-using the older session\u0027s slot and its identifiers (session_id, session_version, etc), which can be used by different SFDP services to identify between specific sessions, even multiple sessions that might have existed on the same 5-tuple at different point in time.\n\nRather than re-using the session slot in this case, I think we should mark the older session for deletion and create a new session entry associated with the new SYN.",
